---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Projects"
  description="Portfolio of AI systems, operations tooling, workflow automation, and implementation case studies."
>
  <div class="container-wide">
    <h1>Projects</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">Examples of turning messy context, repeated work, and agent workflows into systems with review gates, operating docs, and visible outputs.</p>

    <div class="projects-feature-grid">
      <div class="project-card project-card-feature">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3><a href="/knowledge-os-proof/">Signal intake and review system</a></h3>
        </div>
        <p>
          Knowledge OS shows how raw signals, source review, agent work, durable memory, and reviewable artifacts become trusted company knowledge instead of context sprawl.
        </p>
        <div class="card-links">
          <a href="/knowledge-os-proof/">See the system proof &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card project-card-feature">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3><a href="/jules/">Agent-assisted operating loop</a></h3>
        </div>
        <p>
          Jules is the internal operating lab for governed AI workflows: decision support, execution, verification, publishing prep, reporting, and handoffs.
        </p>
        <div class="card-links">
          <a href="/jules/">How it works &rarr;</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules">GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card project-card-feature">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3>Decision advisory workflow</h3>
        </div>
        <p>
          A decision pattern for bringing multiple expert perspectives into one clear recommendation before work begins: domain context, critical review, implementation judgment, and a final human call.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="projects-feature-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
      <div class="project-card project-card-feature">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3><a href="/projects/ava-attendance-officer/">Ava Attendance Officer</a></h3>
          <span class="status status-mixed">Hackathon 2025</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          A multilingual school attendance agent. Connects a teacher dashboard, hall-pass iPad, policy backend, and an OpenAI Realtime voice agent into one working loop. Ava detects overdue passes, evaluates policy thresholds, and calls guardians in English or Spanish.
        </p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span>Python</span><span>FastAPI</span><span>React</span><span>pgvector</span><span>OpenAI Realtime</span><span>WebSocket</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-links">
          <a href="/projects/ava-attendance-officer/">Project details &rarr;</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/hallPassAttendanceOfficer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="projects-grid">
      <div class="project-card card-wide operations-card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3>Operations</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="utility-grid">
          <div class="utility-item">
            <strong>System Admin</strong>
            <p>Local agent infrastructure, service supervision, launchd jobs, Cloudflare deploy paths, credential flow, and the daily plumbing that keeps an AI business running.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="utility-item">
            <strong>Event Management</strong>
            <p>Event setup, publishing, scheduling, RSVP flow, follow-up materials, and the coordination work behind public demos and operating-system launches.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="utility-item">
            <strong>Utilities</strong>
            <p>Small tools that remove friction: Whisper repetition cleanup, Plane sync, markdown workflows, credential helpers, and automation scripts for recurring work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
